✅ What we did in Govern Node (Simple Explanation)
🎯 Purpose of Govern Node

To manage, review, and approve the ML model before production (like a control/checkpoint layer).

🧱 Step 1: Registered the Model
Took the trained model (Random Forest)
Added it to Model Registry (Govern node)

👉 Meaning:
The model is now tracked and managed centrally

🏛️ Step 2: Applied Governance Workflow
Created a governed project using Dataiku Standard template
This automatically created lifecycle stages:
Development
Review
Deployment
Production

👉 Meaning:
Model must go through approval steps before production

👤 Step 3: Assigned Roles for Approval
Assigned roles like:
Business reviewer
Risk & Compliance
IT / Operations

👉 Meaning:
Different teams are responsible for approving the model

✔️ Step 4: Completed Review & Approval
Approved the model (self or assigned role)
Workflow moved forward:
Development → Review → Approved

👉 Meaning:
Model passed governance checks

🚀 Step 5: Promoted Model Across Stages

You moved the model through:

Review → Deployment
Deployment → Production

👉 Meaning:
Model is now approved for production use

🔍 What Governance Ensures
Model is validated before use
Proper approvals are recorded
Full audit trail exists
Compliance with enterprise policies
